=======
Ubuntu
=======

If you do not have `Virtualbox <https://www.virtualbox.org>`_ installed, please open the software center, in Unity, Ubuntu Software Center should be a default item in the launcher.

Alternatively, search for “software” in the Dash search field. 

Now search in the right top corner for *virtualbox*.

.. thumbnail:: ../_static/virtualbox_install_ubuntu_sc.png
   :width: 697px
   :height: 392px
   :align: center

Click on install 

.. thumbnail:: ../_static/virtualbox_install_ubuntu_passwd.png
   :width: 697px
   :height: 392px
   :align: center

Enter your password

.. thumbnail:: ../_static/virtualbox_ubuntu_install_installing.png
   :width: 697px
   :height: 392px
   :align: center

Wait till installation is done, this can take some minutes, depending on your network and computer.

If you wish to install it via command-line please do:

.. code-block:: bash

    $ sudo apt-get install virtualbox

After the installation is done continue with :ref:`starting-reference-label`.